{0 day11-batch}

Batch orchestration for documentation builds. {!Day11_batch.Targets} resolves CLI
arguments into a list of packages to process, supporting explicit
targets, JSON file input, small-universe mode, and all-versions mode.
{!Day11_batch.Incremental_solver} caches solver results keyed by opam-repo commit
SHA and reuses solutions whose examined package set does not overlap
with changed packages, avoiding redundant re-solving across runs.
{!Day11_batch.Blessing} selects the canonical documentation universe for each
package when it appears in multiple solutions, using a heuristic that
maximizes dependency count for richer docs. {!Day11_batch.Rerun} rebuilds failed
layers and cascades recovery to dependents whose failing dependency has
since succeeded. {!Day11_batch.Summary} aggregates build and doc outcomes, records
per-package history, generates the status index, and prints a
human-readable summary. {!Day11_batch.Profile} manages named analysis
configurations (repositories, targets, platform settings) stored as
JSON files. {!Day11_batch.Profile_ctx} is the resolved context that
pairs a profile with everything derived from it — loaded git package
index, resolved repo SHAs, opam env, base layer, build env, shared
hash cache — so downstream build/doc APIs take one value instead of
a long list of profile-shaped arguments. {!Day11_batch.Snapshot}
captures point-in-time state of all opam repositories within a
profile, keyed by commit SHAs.

Sits near the top of the dependency hierarchy, depending on
{!day11-opam-build}, {!page-solution}, {!day11-lib}, {!day11-layer},
and {!day11-sys}.

